This Privacy Policy (“Policy”) applies to PolyBuzz, an online chatting tool, as well as related contents, tools, features and functionality (together, the “Services”) provided by CLOUD WHALE INTERACTIVE TECHNOLOGY LLC (“we”, “our” or “us”). This Policy is hereby formulated by us in accordance with applicable laws to protect personal information of users (“you” or “your”).
Scope and Consent
This Policy sets out why, how and what personal information we collect, use, store, process, share, transfer and publicly disclose about you, the information security protection measures we take, and the rights we honor for your access, update, deletion and control of your personal information. Please read this Policy in combination with PolyBuzz
Terms of Use
. If you do not agree to this Policy, you shall stop using PolyBuzz and/or our Services.
We reserve the right to amend this Policy at any time and from time to time, and we encourage you to regularly review this Policy to get the latest revision. If you do not accept the Policy as amended, you shall stop using PolyBuzz.
The Services are not designed for minors under 14, and our Terms of Service prohibit use by anyone under 14 or under 16 if you are a resident of the European Economic Area.
We will provide a child user, defined by Children's Online Privacy Protection Rule ("COPPA"), with our Services only after his/her parent or guardian has read this Policy, fully acknowledged and agreed to all the terms herein, and given consent required by applicable laws. Unless otherwise permitted or required by law, we will not collect, use, or disclose any personal information of a child user without obtaining consent from that child’s parent or guardian. Parents can review personal information collected about the child user, have the information deleted, and request us to discontinue collection or use of the child’s personal information.
By accessing and/or using our Services, you confirm that you are either an adult at or over the age of majority in your jurisdiction, or a child under your parent or legal guardian’s supervision, and that you have the right, authority, capacity or consent to access and/or use our Services and agree to abide by this Policy.
This Policy is an electronic contract formed under applicable laws, and does not require any physical, electronic or digital signature.
Please read this Policy carefully. By accessing or using PolyBuzz and/or our Services, you agree and acknowledge that you understand, agree and consent to this Policy and to the collection, use, process, share, transfer and disclosure of information about you that you have provided or may in the future provide to us for the purposes set out in this Policy and in accordance with applicable laws.
Collection and Use of User Information
We will collect personal information (sometimes may include
sensitive personal data
) from you for the purpose hereof and in line with the principles of legality, legitimacy, necessity, and transparency. If we use personal information about you for any purpose other than those contained herein, or collect personal information from you for any other purposes, we will notify you in a reasonable manner and obtain your prior consent as required under applicable laws. We do not require you to disclose more information than reasonably necessary.
In USA, “
Sensitive Personal Data
” is defined to include ten specified categories of data that may be maintained or collected by U.S. businesses.  The categories of data include types of financial, geolocation, and health data, among others.  Moreover, a U.S. business that maintains or collects these categories of data on U.S. citizens will only be considered to have sensitive personal data to the extent it (i) targets or tailors products or services to certain populations, including U.S. military members and employees of federal agencies with national security responsibilities, (ii) collects or maintains such data on at least one million individuals, or (iii) has a demonstrated business objective to maintain or collect such data on greater than one million individuals and such data is an integrated part of the U.S. business’s primary products or services.  Genetic test information is also included in the definition regardless of whether it meets (i), (ii), or (iii)
In EU, the following personal data is considered ‘
sensitive
’ and is subject to specific processing conditions: 1) personal data revealing racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs; 2) trade-union membership; 3) genetic data, biometric data processed solely to identify a human being; 4) health-related data; 5) data concerning a person’s sex life or sexual orientation.
We may synchronize user personal information on your different mobile devices to ensure smooth user experience.
Personal information you provide during use of PolyBuzz
We respect user privacy and are committed to reasonably protect it in all material respects. You agree that we may collect the following personal information about you:
Information necessary to provide, maintain and improve PolyBuzz and/or our Services;
Information knowingly supplied by you; information collected with your consent;
Information collected from other sources in line with this Policy (e.g., third-party service providers or social media platforms).
“Personal Information” means any information, whether true or not, about an individual who can be identified (a) from that data; or (b) from that data or other information to which we have or are likely to have access, including data in our records as may be updated from time to time.
2.1.2 By registering an account with PolyBuzz, or accessing or using PolyBuzz (with or without a user account), you consent to provide us necessary information including your personal information as described herein.
User personal information that we may collect include, but is not limited to:
email address;
username;
uploaded pictures or input text;
purchase and payment records;
device information;
log information;
precise geolocation information;
your Contacts.
The following describes the extent to which your personal information may be required and collected.
2.1.2.1 Registration
You may log in with your current Google, or Apple account. When you do so, a PolyBuzz account will be automatically created. You may create a new account through your email and follow our registration steps.
Please note that as an unregistered user, you may not be able to use certain features of PolyBuzz, but you may browse the contents and use the AI Chatting features with limitations.
2.1.2.2 Profile creation
To ensure your pleasant experience with PolyBuzz, you can, but are not required to, provide a username to create a profile. If you do not create a personal profile with optional information, you will still enjoy the basic functions.
2.1.2.3 AI Chatting
When you use the “AI Chatting” feature, you can choose from the following three (2) ways to initiate a chat:
Create an AI character via our AI algorithm;
Find an existing AI character on our server.
Therefore, if you do not allow access to your album, device internal storage, keyboard (for text inputs), or microphone (for voice inputs), we may not be able to offer you this feature.
We may also access your precise geolocation information (through your device) to provide a customized AI Chatting experience based on more accurate simulations to your local environment.
2.1.2.4 Online Payment
We offer value-added premium services, for which you need to pay in the one of the following two (2) ways:
In-app purchase by credit card; or
through a third party (such as Apple Pay, Google Pay, etc.)
As a result of your payment, we may collect some financial information (e.g., payment records or other payment-related data).
2.1.2.5 Customer Service
When you contact our customer service, you may need to provide your account information for identify verification. In addition, you may need to submit relevant evidence (including but not limited to pictures or texts) and contact information. Without such information, we may not be able to respond to you promptly or assist you as desired.
2.1.2.6 User Consent
You will be asked to consent to the following:
photos/storage: to collect the photos that you wish to upload and display to other users, or train our AI algorithm (photos will be uploaded to our back-end server)
Microphone: to input texts via voice input feature
Internet access: to view WLAN state and network connections to optimize Internet access by cellular network status camera: to take photos and/or videos for your questions identity: to link to and enable login through a third-party account (e.g., Google or Apple)
precise geolocation: to train our AI algorithm
Contacts: to provide an easy way for you to screen if any of your contact persons are using PolyBuzz, and establish connections within PolyBuzz
PolyBuzz also requests your permission for flashlight and alarm wake lock, which do not collect user personal information.
2.2 User Information Automatically Collected
To safeguard the security of your account and better serve you, we will collect and use the following information generated during your use of PolyBuzz, but only to the extent permitted under applicable laws.
2.2.1 Device Information
When you use PolyBuzz, we will collect certain of your device information, including device ID, IMEI, OAID, MAC, browser type, operator information and usage, information about device location (IP address), device model, operating system version, IDFA (for iOS only), IDFV (for iOS only), Android ID (for Android only). Such information is the unique identification of the device, and we may combine it with other personal information we collect so that we can provide consistent Services.
2.2.2 Log Information
PolyBuzz will automatically collect and save user network logs, including browser type, browsing records, network diagnosis, so that we can evaluate use of PolyBuzz, optimize it and improve our Services.
2.3 User Information Obtained from Third Parties
2.3.1 We may collect and use user personal information from a third party upon your consent. We process your personal information in accordance with the contract with the third party and applicable laws, and we ask that you carefully read the service agreement and privacy policy of such third party. Your refusal to a third party’s collection, use or sending of your personal information may result in failure to use PolyBuzz. Please note that we do not condition your use of our Services on the disclosure of more personal information than is reasonably necessary.
2.3.2 When You log into PolyBuzz through a social media plug-in, you will be redirected to the third-party platform, where you can register or log into an account thereof. When logging in through the registered account of a permitted third party, your profile of that third-party account will be bound with an automatically created PolyBuzz account. Currently, we offer social media sign-in for Google and Apple users. Through the link between two accounts, we only collect user name and profile picture from the third-party account. Please note that even if the third-party provider may collect your device version, system version, generated ID, phone style, phone name, ICCID (for iOS only), BSSID (for iOS only), MAC (for iOS only), IMSI (for iOS only), IMEI (for iOS only) for their purpose, such information will not be needed by and transferred to us.
WE HAVE NO CONTROL OVER AND ASSUME NO RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE CONTENT, PRIVACY POLICIES OR PRACTICES OF ANY THIRD-PARTY WEBSITES AND MOBILE APPLICATIONS OR ANY SERVICES OFFERED BY SUCH THIRD PARTIES. YOU AGREE THAT WE WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY BREACH OF YOUR ’S PRIVACY OF PERSONAL INFORMATION NOR FOR ANY LOSS INCURRED TO YOU AS A RESULT OF USE OF SUCH THIRD-PARTY PRODUCTS OR SERVICES.
2.3.3 When You pay for our premium services through a third party, we will collect your user’s name, profile picture and payment record from the third party.
2.4 Exceptions to Acquiring User Consent
Subject to applicable laws, we may not need to obtain your consent when collecting and using your personal information, but only if:
it is related to performance of the obligations required by applicable laws;
it is directly related to national security, public safety, public health, or significant public interests;
it is directly related to crime investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgment, or is required by the competent authorities or other circumstances required by applicable laws including but not limited to in response to court orders and subpoenas;
it is required for safeguarding a user’s life, property and other significant legal interests but it is difficult to obtain your consent, or we have reason to believe that someone is or may be causing injury to or interference with our rights or property, other users, or anyone else that could be harmed by such activities;
the information was made available to the general public by yourself;
it is necessary for execution and performance of a contract between you and us per your request;
the information is collected from legally and publicly disclosed channels, such as legal news reports, published government information or other channels;
it is necessary for maintaining the operation of PolyBuzz, such as troubleshooting, discovering and resolving issues in relation with PolyBuzz and/or our Services; or
other circumstances specified or permitted under applicable laws.
Cookies, SDKs and Similar Technologies
Cookies
A cookie is a data file, often including a unique identifier, that is sent to your browser from a web server and is then stored on the hard drive of your device.
We only use strictly necessary cookies. These cookies are essential in order to enable you to move around in PolyBuzz and use its features, such as remembering your log-in status and accessing secure areas. Without these cookies, certain services you ask for cannot be provided. These cookies do not contain any personal information. We use these cookies to remember the way you log in (by email, Google or Apple account) and provide our Services accordingly.
SDKs
An SDK (Software Development Kit) is a collection of software tools, libraries, documentation, code samples, and sometimes APIs (Application Programming Interfaces) that developers use to create applications for specific platforms, frameworks, or devices. SDKs make it easier to integrate certain features or functionalities into an app without building them from scratch.
Our application integrates third-party Software Development Kits (SDKs) to enhance its functionality and provide certain features. These SDKs may collect information automatically, such as:
Device identifiers (e.g., IMEI, MAC address, advertising ID)
Usage data (e.g., app interactions, session duration)
Technical data (e.g., IP address, operating system, device type, mobile network information)
Location information, if you grant permission
The data collected by these SDKs is used to improve user experience, provide analytics, serve advertisements, or enable features like in-app purchases. We ensure that any third-party SDK we integrate complies with applicable data protection laws and has a robust privacy policy governing the collection and use of data.
Please note that the privacy practices of these third parties are not controlled by us, and we encourage you to review their privacy policies for further details.
Advertising
We may allow third-party advertising networks to place cookies or other tracking technologies on your computer, mobile phone, or other device to collect information about your use of the Services in order to (a) inform, optimize, and serve marketing content based on past visits to our website and other online services and (b) report how our marketing content impressions and interactions with these marketing impressions are related to visits to our online services.
Our third-party operators may provide you with an ad based on your data includes GAID (Google Advertising ID on Android devices) or IDFA (Identifier for Advertising on IOS devices), region, location information and IP address. This Policy does not govern Third-party Operators, as they have their own privacy policies (such as TopOn:
https://help.toponad.com/docs/Privacy-Policy
).
You may receive advertising on your computer through a web browser. Cookies may be associated with de-identified data linked to or derived from data you voluntarily have submitted to us (e.g., your email address) that we may disclose to a vendor in hashed, non-human-readable form.
You have the right to “opt-out” the customized advertising. By doing so, you will receive standardized advertisement that may not fit in your interest. To opt-out the customized advertising, you need to file a request to us by the ways set forth in the “Contact Us” section below, and specify on the subject line “Opt-out Request”.
