To fully enjoy PolyBuzz, you may need to provide some basic personal information. If you want to withdraw certain consent, you may do so in the “Settings” menu. Alternatively, you may contact us for assistance.
Please note that after you withdraw or modify the scope of consent, we will no longer collect and use the pertinent personal information about you, and we may not be able to continue our Services to you. However, withdrawal or change to the scope of your consent will not affect our collection, processing and storage of your user information obtained on your prior consent unless such information is deleted from PolyBuzz.
7.3 Account Deletion
7.3.1 To delete your PolyBuzz account, you may go to the “Setting” page, and then click “Account” – “Delete”.
7.3.2 Unless otherwise required by applicable laws, we may not delete certain user information from the backup system immediately but will do so when the backup system is updated or upgraded.
7.3.3 Deletion of your account is irreversible, and upon deletion you may no longer enjoy all contents or functions of PolyBuzz. Please be cautious when choosing to delete your account.
7.4 Respond to User Requests
7.4.1 When you contact us to exercise the user rights set out in Sections 7.1 through 7.3 above, we will need to verify your identity before processing your request. During the identification process, it is vital that you provide and keep a valid email, ideally the same email that you registered your account. We will respond as soon as possible and generally no more than 30 days from receipt of your request and verification of your identity.
7.4.2 We do not ordinarily charge any fee for dealing with user inquiries and/or requests to the extent commercially reasonable. We reserve the right to refuse any request that:
is not directly associated with you;
is repetitive without good cause;
needs excessive technical investment (for example, to develop new systems or fundamentally change existing business practices);
threatens the legal rights and/or interests of others;
is impossible, impractical, or unreasonable to implement;
or is in violation of our Terms of Use, this Policy and applicable laws.
Retention of User Information
8.1 All user personal information will be retained for no longer than is necessary for the purposes that are stated herein or that you have authorized, unless otherwise set forth in these Terms and/or required or permitted by applicable laws.
8.2 We will also retain usage data for internal analysis purposes. Usage data is generally retained for a shorter period, except when this data is used to strengthen the security or to improve the functionality of PolyBuzz, or when we are legally obligated to retain this data for longer time periods.
8.3 We reserve the right to retain the aggregated and anonymized data derived from user personal information for any purpose (commercial and non-commercial) as we deem fit and proper.
Please note that such anonymous data may be derived from your or your child’s personal information, but will not be considered personal information at law if it will not be linked to you or your child personally and cannot be used to identify you or your child.
Security of User Information
9.1 We use appropriate organizational, technical, and physical safeguards to protect user information. We have adopted protective measures at multiple levels (e.g., industry-standard technical security measures, supporting organizational structures and management systems) to prevent, to the maximum extent technically practical, user information from leakage, destruction, misuse, unauthorized access, unauthorized disclosure or modification.
9.2 THE SECURITY OF USER INFORMATION IS VERY IMPORTANT TO US, BUT PLEASE BE REMINDED THAT NO METHOD OF TRANSMISSION OVER THE INTERNET OR METHOD OF ELECTRONIC STORAGE IS 100% SECURE. WHILE WE STRIVE TO USE COMMERCIALLY VIABLE MEANS TO PROTECT USER PERSONAL INFORMATION, WE CANNOT GUARANTEE ITS ABSOLUTE SECURITY.
9.3 In the event of a data breach, we will carry out an assessment expeditiously. If the breach results in, or is likely to result in, significant harm to affected individuals, or is, or is likely to be, of a significant scale, we will notify the relevant authorities and our users as soon as it is practicable to do so, and in any event, no later than the mandatory time limit under applicable laws.
International Transfer of User Information
Subject to applicable laws, user personal information may be transferred and processed outside of your local jurisdiction. We will endeavor to ensure appropriate safeguards so that user information will remain protected in accordance with this Policy and applicable laws.
We will take reasonably necessary steps to ensure that your personal information is treated securely and in accordance with this Policy and applicable laws, and no transfer of your personal information will be made to an organization or a country unless there is adequate security control in place.
Protection of Child Users’ Personal Information
The Services are not designed for minors under 14, and our Terms of Service prohibit use by anyone under 14 or under 16 if you are a resident of the European Economic Area. If we discover that an individual under 14 has provided us with “personal information,” as defined in the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”), we will close the account and delete the personal information to the extent required by COPPA. We may, where permitted by law, retain certain information internally for purposes described in this Policy.
You confirm that you are the parent of the child who uses PolyBuzz or an adult user at or above the minimum age permitted to use services like ours in your jurisdiction. If you do not acknowledge and agree to this Policy, please do not use PolyBuzz and/or our Services and we will not collect personal information from you or your child.
Regional Privacy Disclosures
Residents of the European Economic Area and United Kingdom
PolyBuzz is considered the “data controller” of the “personal data” (as defined under the General Data Protection Regulation, GDPR) we handle under this Policy. In other words, PolyBuzz is responsible for deciding how to collect, use, and disclose personal data, subject to applicable law. The laws of the European Economic Area and the United Kingdom require data controllers to tell you about the legal ground that they rely on for using, sharing, or disclosing your personal data. To the extent those laws apply, our legal grounds are as follows:
Contractual Commitments: We may use, share, or disclose personal data to honor our contractual commitments to you. For example, we will process your personal data to comply with our agreements with you, and to honor our commitments in any contracts that we have with you.
With Your Consent: Where required by law, and in some other cases, we use, share, or disclose personal data on the basis of your consent.
Legitimate Interests: In many cases, we use, share, or disclose personal data on the ground that it furthers our legitimate business interests in ways that are not overridden by the interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the affected individuals, such as customer service, certain promotional activities, analyzing and improving our business, providing security for the Services, preventing fraud, and managing legal issues.
Legal Compliance: We need to use and disclose personal data in certain ways to comply with our legal obligations.
In addition to those rights described herein, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the relevant supervisory authority. However, we encourage you to contact us first, and we will do our very best to resolve your concern.
Residents of California
Starting on January 1, 2020, the California Consumer Privacy Act (“CCPA”) governs how businesses handle the personal information of California residents. CCPA was amended by the adoption of the Consumer Privacy Rights Act (“CPRA”) effective March 29, 2023. At PolyBuzz, we are committed to our subscribers’ success, including their compliance efforts with respect to the CCPA. We’re here to assist our subscribers with their efforts to comply with the CCPA.
For PolyBuzz’s subscribers, PolyBuzz is a “service provider” under the CCPA. We process personal information only on behalf of our subscribers, pursuant to written contracts. Those contracts, which are already in place, permit PolyBuzz to process our subscribers’ data (including personal information) only for the purpose of providing our services. While we necessarily have to process personal information transmitted through our network, we do not sell that information to third parties.
The CCPA sets forth certain obligations for businesses that “sell” or “share” personal information. Where we refer to “sell” or “share” (or their variants) in quotes, we are referring to those terms as uniquely defined in the CCPA.
We may use third-party analytics services and online advertising services that may result in the “sharing” of online identifiers (e.g., cookie data, IP addresses, device identifiers, general location information, and usage information) with advertising partners to advertise the Services on other websites. If you or your authorized agent would like to opt out of our “sharing” of your information for such purposes, you may do so by go to “settings” on our website or in-app and disable the data sharing. We do not knowingly “sell” or “share” the personal information of children under 17.
If you are an individual seeking to exercise your rights under the CCPA (as amended by the CRPA) please see our Privacy Policy for more information. We updated our Privacy Policy periodically to align with the requirements of the CPRA to better provide you with information about how PolyBuzz collects your personal information and how to exercise your rights with respect to that information.
If you or anyone in your organization has questions about how PolyBuzz helps your organization comply with the CCPA, contact:
legal
@mail.polybuzz.ai
Residents of Nevada
If you are a resident of Nevada, you have the right to opt-out of the sale of certain personal information to unaffiliated parties. You can exercise this right by contacting us as described in the “Contact Us” section below with the subject line “Nevada Do Not Sell Request” and providing us with your name and the email address. We do not currently sell your personal information as sales are defined in Nevada Revised Statutes Chapter 603A.
Residents of Brazilian
We are committed to complying with the Brazilian General Data Protection Law (LGPD) regarding the collection, use, and protection of personal data for users located in Brazil. Other than the detailed explanations of how we handle your personal data in this Privacy Policy, as a Brazilian user, you have the following rights regarding your personal data under the LGPD: 1) Right to Confirmation: You have the right to know whether we process any of your personal data. 2) Right to Access: You may request access to your personal data and receive a copy of the data we hold about you. 3) Right to Rectification: You can request correction of inaccurate, incomplete, or outdated data. 4) Right to Anonymization, Blocking, or Deletion: You may request the anonymization, blocking, or deletion of unnecessary or excessive data. 5) Right to Data Portability: You have the right to request the transfer of your data to another service provider. 6) Right to Information: You can request information about the entities with whom we have shared your data. 7) Right to Withdraw Consent: You have the right to withdraw your consent at any time when data processing is based on consent. 8) Right to Object to Processing: You can object to certain types of data processing, such as direct marketing or profiling. 9) Right to Review Automated Decisions: You may request a review of decisions made solely on automated processing, which affect your interests.
Residents of Virginia
This section explains the rights of Virginia residents under the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA). As a Virginia resident, you have the following rights regarding your personal data: 1) Right to Access: You have the right to confirm whether we process your personal data and to access such data. 2) Right to Correct: You may request that we correct inaccuracies in the personal data we hold about you. 3) Right to Delete: You can request the deletion of personal data that we have collected from you, subject to certain exceptions. 4) Right to Data Portability: You have the right to obtain a copy of your personal data in a portable and readily usable format. 5) Right to Opt Out of Targeted Advertising, Sale of Personal Data, and Profiling: You may opt out of the processing of your personal data for targeted advertising, the sale of personal data, or profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects.
To exercise your rights under the VCDPA, you may submit a request by contacting us at:
legal
@mail.polybuzz.ai
We will respond to your request within 45 days, as required by the VCDPA. If necessary, we may extend this period by an additional 45 days and will inform you of the extension. If we decline to take action on your request, you may appeal our decision by submitting a written request within a reasonable period. We will review your appeal and provide you with a response within 60 days of receipt.
U
ser’s Right of Remedy
You have the right to seek an effective remedy if your privacy is violated. You may file a complaint with the relevant authorities or pursue legal action to protect your rights. However, if you believe your privacy has been compromised while using PolyBuzz, we encourage you to contact us immediately. We take privacy concerns very seriously and are committed to addressing them promptly. Please refer to the "Contact Us" section below for our contact information.
Contact Us
We have established a department dedicated to user information protection and specially appointed a person responsible for child users’ personal information protection.
Contact Our Data Controller
We have a data management team working and monitoring data 24/7. If you want to contact our Data Controller, you may send an email to:
legal
@mail.polybuzz.ai
and specify on the subjection line “Attn: Data Controller”.
Contact Our Data Protection Officer (DPO)
Our project manager also serves as our Data Protection Officer. If you want to contact our DPO, you may send an email to:
legal
@mail.polybuzz.ai
and specify on the subject line “Attn: DPO”.
Contact Us in General
